half_life_seconds: In monotherapy, the median half-life of alirocumab at steady state was 17Ð20 days in patients receiving alirocumab at SC doses of 75 or 150 mg every 2 weeks. As statin therapy increases the production of PCSK9, statin co-administration is thought to shorten alirocumab half-life; therefore the median apparent half-life of alirocumab was reduced to 12 days at equivalent alirocumab doses. However, this difference is not considered clinically significant and does not change dosing recommendations.

However, this difference is not considered clinically significant and does not change dosing recommendations.
